<poem>
    <metadata>
            <first_line>Four Trees - upon a solitary Acre -</first_line>
            <date period="middle">1863</date>
            <poem_number>J742</poem_number>
            <source>https://www.edickinson.org/editions/2/image_sets/12170725</source>
            <recipient>none</recipient>
            <poem_themes>nature, solitude</poem_themes>
    </metadata>
    
    <body>
        <stanza> 
            <line>Four <nature nature_type="earth">Trees</nature> - upon a <solitude judgment="neutral">solitary</solitude> 
                <nature nature_type="earth">Acre</nature> -</line>
            <line>Without Design</line>
            <line>Or Order, or Apparent <variant>signal</variant> -  <variant>notice</variant> Action -</line>
            <line>Do <variant>reign</variant> - <variant>hinder</variant> - Maintain -</line> <!--elision or intransitive verb? -->
        </stanza> <!--Included judgment because she is making a statement that they are existing just as they are, untouched
            by good or bad -->
        
        <stanza>
            <line><nature nature_type="space">The Sun</nature> - upon a <time>Morning</time> meets them -</line>
            <line><nature nature_type="air">The Wind</nature> -</line>
            <line><solitude>No nearer Neighbor - have they -</solitude></line>
            <line>But <religion religious_type="person">God</religion> -</line>
        </stanza>
        
        <stanza>
            <line>The Acre gives them - Place -</line>
            <line>They - Him - Attention of Passer by -</line> <!--elision here? -->
            <line>Of <darkness>Shadow</darkness>, or of <animal>Squirrel</animal>, haply -</line> 
            <line>Or Boy -</line>
        </stanza>
        
        <stanza>
            <line>What Deed <variant>they bear</variant> is Their's unto the General 
                <nature nature_type="general">Nature</nature> -</line>
            <line>What Plan</line>
            <line>They severally -  <variant>promote - or</variant> retard - or further -</line> <!--elision?-->
            <line><uncertainty>Unknown</uncertainty> -</line>
        </stanza>
    </body>
</poem>

<!--
Four Trees - upon a solitary Acre -
Without Design
Or Order, or Apparent  signal -  notice Action -
Do reign - hinder - Maintain -

The Sun - upon a Morning meets them -
The Wind -
No nearer Neighbor - have they -
But God -

The Acre gives them - Place -
They - Him - Attention of Passer by -
Of Shadow, or of Squirrel, haply -
Or Boy -

What Deed  they bear is Their's unto the General Nature -
What Plan
They severally -  promote - or retard - or further -
Unknown -
-->
